Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease Epidemiology Network) [edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


[re: ProMED-mail Rabies (53): Americas (Costa Rica) bat, human 20181028.6117187]
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Recently, a biologist in [Copey de Dota, in the province of San Jose] Costa Rica acquired rabies while working in a cave. For over 5 decades, Costa Rica has reported the lowest rates of rabies in Central America (El Salvador reports the highest rates), both in terms of cases and cases per 100 000 population [1,2]. Costa Rica also reports the lowest incidence of animal rabies for the region.

See graphs at https://www.gideononline.com/2018/10/28/rabies-in-costa-rica/.

References
----------
1. Berger S. Rabies: Global Status, 2018. 475 pages, 557 graphs, 2570 references
https://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/rabies-global-status/
2. Berger S. Infectious Diseases of Costa Rica, 2018. 334 pages, 120 graphs, 373 references
https://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-costa-rica/
3. Gideon e-Gideon multi-graph tool
https://www.gideononline.com/cases/multi-graphs/

