[We appreciate Dr Berger reminding us of these statistics. While it is true Costa Rica has the lowest reported rate, nevertheless, a bat exposure has occurred. Given the biologist's condition, it is sad, but likely a fatality, based on length of time between the suspected bite and any attempt at treatment. Rabies is fatal without treatment in a timely fashion. - Mod.TG

The clinical course of the biologist who was bitten by a bat in a cave in Copey de Dota, Costa Rica is available in the ProMED-mail post referenced above (20181028.6117187). Rabies is almost always fatal in unvaccinated individuals once symptoms have developed. - Mod.ML

